LAB 4: Topic modeling¶

Use topic models to explore hotel reviews

Objectives:

  • tokenize with MWEs using spacy
  • estimate LDA topic models with tomotopy
  • visualize and evaluate topic models
  • apply topic models to interpretation of hotel reviews

"My husband and I came back from New York last week staying at the Hudson Hotel for 4 nights. The location of the hotel is great but to be honest that was the highlight. \nIt's trying to be modern with escalators in and a great chandelier and dark reception but with scratched paint, peeling walls and too small bedrooms it doesnt live up to the price tag. It's also extremely noisy - there appeared to be some sort of club/nightclub at the back to the late hours and I had to wear earplugs even when reading. \nUnfortunately whilst we were there everything was pretty much closed for refurbishment, not great for New York Xmas time. The 'fantastic' restuarant, glass floored bar and sky terrace all not available (and although it was our travel agents fault for not telling us - we found out ourselves the day before travelling and then couldnt transfer) it did not help that at no point is it mentioned when the sky terrace will close. Apparently it is not available in the winter months - this should be advertised as some of the other hotel terraces are open.\nSo although the location is great, I wouldnt go there again even when it is refurbed. My advice, find something clean and cheap and spend most of the time perusing the city."

In [127]:
def cloud(freqs, title, k=50):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    wc = WordCloud(
        width=750, height=750, background_color="black"
    ).generate_from_frequencies(freqs)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.imshow(wc, interpolation="bilinear")
    plt.show()

Report¶

Finish this notebook by writing a brief report to the hotel managers describing what you've found in the reviews of their hotel, along with some actionable advice. Use whatever data, charts, word clouds, etc. that you think will help you make your case.

This report is on the hotel with offering_id==223023

Bar Chart: The above bar chart depicts that the hotel has more 4 star reviews and similar count of -1,2,3 and 5 star reviews. This shows that the customers of this hotel are not well satisfied with its services.

Word Cloud 1: The first word cloud shows most common topics of hotel reviews with offering id=223023 In the 1st word cloud, we can see that the hotel reviews mostly fall into the topics -'QUITE','DOOR','ITS','DIRTY','BED'

QUITE--"quite, however, bit, much, most, hotels, although, other, ok, nothing”

DOOR-- "door, front_desk, another, never, problem, left, elevator, down, came, check”

DIRTY-- "dirty, bed, old, carpet, smell, over, sheets, looked, worst, door"

ITS-- "its, bar, music, fun, cool, want, club, party, lobby, feel"

BED-- "bed, shower, tv, beds, pillows, lobby, little, too, though, floor”

which indicates that the customers have problem with the cleanliness of the rooms and most customers are describing about bed.

Advise: The managers should concentrate on maintaining clealiness in hotel rooms and providing more sophisticated beds. The manager should also take care about the club section like improving music choices, making it comfortable place, providing variety of drinks etc.

Word Cloud 2: The second word cloud shows most common topics of hotel reviews with offering id=223023 and overall=1 In the wordcloud, we can see that the hotel reviews mostly fall into the topics 'DIRTY' , 'DOOR' , 'HE', 'THEM', 'BECAUSE'

DOOR "door, front_desk, another, never, problem, left, elevator, down, came, check”

DIRTY "dirty, bed, old, carpet, smell, over, sheets, looked, worst, door"

HE "he, she, told, said, asked, called, front_desk, her, went, his”

THEM "them, over, their, off, am, never, should, then, still, charged”

BECAUSE "because, am, their, since, them, sure, way, make, find, want”

which indicates that the customers are mainly facing problem with cleanliness

Advise: improve cleanliness

Word Cloud 3: The 3rd word cloud shows most common topics of hotel reviews with offering id=223023 and overall=5 In the word cloud we can see that the hotel reviews mostly fall into the topics ‘BEST’ , ‘NYC’ , ‘ITS’ , ‘QUITE’ , ‘LOVED’ BEST "best, ever, amazing, beautiful, every, most, perfect, love, wonderful, say”

NYC "nyc, times_square, new_york, subway, central_park, manhattan, ny, close, broadway,midtown”

ITS "its, bar, music, fun, cool, want, club, party, lobby, feel”

QUITE "quite, however, bit, much, most, hotels, although, other, ok, nothing”

LOVED "loved, chicago, definitely, nicely, decorated, beautiful, enjoyed, weekend, perfect, everything”

which indicates that the hotels in NYC and Chicago are well maintained and customers are satisfied with hotel services. The customers who gave 5 star review to this hotel loves the hotel bar.

Advise: Managers need to continue this NYC and Chicago to attract more customers.
